                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                  <td class="p-4 font-medium">Student Portal</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center text-red-500">✗</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center text-green-500">✓</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center text-green-500">✓</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="p-4 font-medium">Reporting</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center text-red-500">✗</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center text-green-500">✓</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center text-green-500">✓</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                  <td class="p-4 font-medium">Support</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center">Email only</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center">Full</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-center">Priority</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Free vs Paid Real Costs -->
        <div id="free-vs-paid" class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">The Real Cost of "Free" Software</h2>

          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Free software has hidden costs that aren't immediately obvious. Here's what you're actually trading when you choose free over paid:
          </p>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-red-100">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-4">Hidden Costs of Free</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-3">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Time spent on admin:</strong> Manual data entry, phone calls for bookings, chasing payments—easily 5+ hours/week</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Lost revenue from no-shows:</strong> Without automated reminders, no-show rates are 15-25% higher</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Missed bookings:</strong> Students who can't book online often go elsewhere</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Unprofessional image:</strong> Basic tools can make your business look amateur</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-green-100">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-4">Value of Paid Software</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-3">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Time saved:</strong> Automation saves 5-10 hours per week on admin</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Reduced no-shows:</strong> Automated reminders cut no-shows by 50-80%</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>24/7 booking:</strong> Students book when convenient—including evenings</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Professional image:</strong> Online booking and portals build trust</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-brand-navy text-white rounded-xl p-6 mt-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Quick Calculation</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
              If your hourly rate is £35 and free software costs you 5 extra hours of admin per week, that's £175/week or £700/month in lost teaching time. Most paid software costs £30-50/month.
            </p>
            <p class="font-bold text-brand-red-light">
              The maths rarely favours free software once you have more than a handful of students.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Common Limitations -->
        <div id="limitations" class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Common Limitations of Free Plans</h2>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Student Limits</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Most free plans cap active students at 5-10. Once you exceed this, you'll need to delete old students to add new ones—losing valuable lesson history and progress records.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">No Online Booking</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Students can't book themselves. This means phone calls, WhatsApp messages, and back-and-forth to find times that work. Many potential students will simply book with a competitor who offers online booking.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-6 py-2">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Manual Reminders</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">You'll need to send your own text or email reminders before lessons. Miss one, and you risk a no-show—costing you an hour of income plus wasted travel time.</p>
            </div>

